        "message": "RakuAST: Inline a dot-assignment past its dispatcher\n\nPreviously a `.=` dot-assignment compiled to a `dispatch:<.=>` callmethod\nthat does the method call and the store back in one dispatcher, and that\ndispatcher stays in the QAST to run on every use.\n\nThe optimize pass now rewrites it to a plain method call whose result is\nstored back with `p6store`, the same shape the legacy frontend reaches in\n`optimize_dot_equals_method_call`. Both the explicit form (`$x .= meth`)\nand a bare call on the topic (`.=meth`, including the `with`, `without`,\nand `andthen`/`orelse` modifier forms) are handled. A target that is not\na plain variable is bound to a temporary so it is evaluated once. The\nrewrite is gated on optimization being on.",
        "tree": {
